ion criteria passed:\n    23ŌåÆ1. Ō£ģ go build ./cmd/rick succeeds\n    24ŌåÆ2. Ō£ģ --version outputs 0.1.0\n    25ŌåÆ3. Ō£ģ --help shows all commands\n    26ŌåÆ4. Ō£ģ --verbose flag works\n    27ŌåÆ5. Ō£ģ init --help works\n    28ŌåÆ6. Ō£ģ plan --help works\n    29ŌåÆ7. Ō£ģ doing --help works\n    30ŌåÆ8. Ō£ģ learning --help works\n    31ŌåÆ9. Ō£ģ --job flag works\n    32ŌåÆ10. Ō£ģ --dry-run flag works\n    33ŌåÆ\n    34ŌåÆ## Architecture Notes\n    35ŌåÆ\n    36ŌåÆ- Cobra provides automatic help generation and command routing\n    37ŌåÆ- Global flags are defined on root command with PersistentFlags\n    38ŌåÆ- Each command is in its own file under internal/cmd/\n    39ŌåÆ- Commands can access global flags via GetVerbose() and GetDryRun() helper functions\n    40ŌåÆ\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fc16ff6-dedc-4ae8-8182-4c66dc8e5594","uuid":"48c1b822-0422-4968-be61-03ce3c080b9a","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sunquan/.claude/projects/-Users-sunquan-ai-coding-CODING-rick--morty/memory/MEMORY.md","content":"# Rick CLI Project Memory\n\n## Completed Work\n\n### Job 2: Cobra CLI Framework (Ō£ģ Completed)\n\n**Structure**:\n- `cmd/rick/main.go` - Entry point, creates root command and calls Execute()\n- `internal/cmd/root.go` - Root command with global flags (--verbose, --dry-run, --version)\n- `internal/cmd/init.go` - Init command\n- `internal/cmd/plan.go` - Plan command with --job flag\n- `internal/cmd/doing.go` - Doing command with --job flag\n- `internal/cmd/learning.go` - Learning command with --job flag\n\n**Key Features**:\n- VERSION constant (0.1.0) defined in main.go\n- All commands use RunE instead of Run for error handling\n- Global flags available to all commands via GetVerbose() and GetDryRun()\n- All commands support --verbose and --dry-run flags\n- --help auto-generated by Cobra\n\n**Testing**: All 10 validation criteria passed:\n1. Ō£ģ go build ./cmd/rick succeeds\n2. Ō£ģ --version outputs 0.1.0\n3. Ō£ģ --help shows all commands\n4. Ō£ģ --verbose flag works\n5. Ō£ģ init --help works\n6. Ō£ģ plan --help works\n7. Ō£ģ doing --help works\n8. Ō£ģ learning --help works\n9. Ō£ģ --job flag works\n10. Ō£ģ --dry-run flag works\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n- Cobra provides automatic help generation and command routing\n- Global flags are defined on root command with PersistentFlags\n- Each command is in its own file under internal/cmd/\n- Commands can access global flags via GetVerbose() and GetDryRun() helper functions\n","numLines":40,"startLine":1,"totalLines":40}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"stop_reason":null,"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_a12c8b2c-788","type":"message","content":[{"input":{"file_path":"/Users/sunquan/ai_coding/CODING/rick/.morty"},"name":"Read","id":"toolu_bdrk_011m9o62B3V2eXZ365UWffsp","type":"tool_use"}],"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fc16ff6-dedc-4ae8-8182-4c66dc8e5594","uuid":"bbbb3118-d7f8-4b7a-bf81-7ce816da1ceb"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","content":"EISDIR: illegal operation on a directory, read '/Users/sunquan/ai_coding/CODING/rick/.morty'","is_error":true,"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011m9o62B3V2eXZ365UWffsp"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fc16ff6-dedc-4ae8-8182-4c66dc8e5594","uuid":"2a375df1-a5a1-4a89-835c-e22aaba15892","tool_use_result":"Error: EISDIR: illegal operation on a directory, read '/Users/sunquan/ai_coding/CODING/rick/.morty'"},{"type":"assistant","mes